	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have this sword, and I use it in conjunction with a shield, being able to BASH with it, and I do about 13 damage max with it.  The neatest thing about it is that it is a little stronger than a regular short sword, and it is stronger too.  I use it whenever I need to pull out my shield; Otherwise, I use my Claymore.  This is also a good one to interrupt casters, and BASHing them isn't fun for them either.  Think about it: you will interrupt them with the Stoutbite, and then you stun them. Since i am a Paladin, I can cast spells, and I have noticed that when I cast a spell using my Claymore it takes a lot longet to hit the enemy afterwards. But, when I use this one, I slash, cast, slash, slash, etc. while they are trying to keep up! The damage is usually offset by the shield's BASHing, too, so I get more damage than others might. This is a good sword to have if you just can't afford a faast one yet; it will get you used to using fast swords.  <BR>

				</font>
			</td>

